{"id":"317078239_Engineering_RGB_color_vision_into_Escherichia_coli","abstract":"Optogenetic tools use colored light to rapidly control gene expression in space and time. We designed a genetically encoded system that gives Escherichia coli the ability to distinguish between red, green, and blue (RGB) light and respond by changing gene expression. We use this system to produce 'color photographs' on bacterial culture plates by controlling pigment production and to redirect metabolic flux by expressing CRISPRi guide RNAs. Â© 2017 Nature America, Inc., part of Springer Nature. All rights reserved.","authors":["Jesus Fernandez-Rodriguez","Felix Moser","Miryoung Song","Christopher A Voigt"],"meta":["May 2017Nature Chemical Biology 13(7)","DOI:10.1038/nchembio.2390"],"references":["309919689_An_open-hardware_platform_for_optogenetics_and_photobiology","289999583_Reversible_Optogenetic_Control_of_Subcellular_Protein_Localization_in_a_Live_Vertebrate_Embryo","279299914_A_predictive_biophysical_model_of_translational_coupling_to_coordinate_and_control_protein_expression_in_bacterial_operons","264351196_A_'resource_allocator'_for_transcription_based_on_a_highly_fragmented_T7_RNA_polymerase","261515238_A_green-light_inducible_lytic_system_for_cyanobacterial_cells","260379425_Eukaryotic_algal_phytochromes_span_the_visible_spectrum","235773961_Repurposing_CRISPR_as_an_RNA-Guided_Platform_for_Sequence-Specific_Control_of_Gene_Expression","235372038_Switchable_Gene_Expression_in_Escherichia_coli_Using_a_Miniaturized_Photobioreactor","221747877_From_Dusk_Till_Dawn_One-Plasmid_Systems_for_Light-Regulated_Gene_Expression_vol_416_pg_534_2012","47643888_Designing_and_engineering_evolutionary_robust_genetic_circuits","26327796_A_Synthetic_Genetic_Edge_Detection_Program","24445754_The_second_wave_of_synthetic_biology_From_modules_to_systems","7461849_Engineering_Escherichia_coli_to_see_light","6171567_Minimizing_acetate_formation_in_E_coli_fermentations","5230198_Cyanobacteriochrome_CcaS